This paper discusses the implementation of efficient multigrid preconditioners for elliptic partial differential equations (PDEs) using a framework that allows the expression of each component of the algorithm at the correct abstraction level. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to atmospheric modeling, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Mathematical Software (cs.MS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
